The Kimber Bel Air Ultra II single stage, match grade aluminum trigger is a joy to pull, especially over the mushy triggers seen on most double action pistols. The 4 to 5lbs pull is steady and smooth, while the reset is short and crisp. This is a gun that fires naturally, even for beginner's that have "low and left" trigger slap tendencies. Many shooters actually prefer this style over the bulkier ambidextrous paddles. postcontent: For sale is a wickedly cool customized M&P 45C. When this gun was new, it was sent to Robar for their Tricon rebuild. They no longer do this rebuild on the M&P but they are doing this on the Glock 19 currently (see second pic). Their price to do this rebuild on YOUR Glock is $1995!! At the time, this rebuild on the M&P was ~$1250. I am sure the price differential is due to them doing a bit more customizing machining on the Glock slide along with inflation.Highlights of this rebuild include machining of the slide to accommodate a Trijicon along with installing one, relocation of the rear sight for co-witness, a trigger job (this one has the best trigger I have ever felt on a polymer gun, a sentiment shared by everyone who has handled it), custom stippling job (even on the extra backstraps) and refinishing the slide in the Robar treatment. All in all, it made this 45C the ultimate in a polymer carry 45.I picked this up on trade, have run about 100 flawless rounds through it and then let it sit in the gunsafe. Time to move it on to someone who will use it and free us some cash for my next project. I realized I am just not a guy who wants an optic on his carry gun.Included with this are the original S&W plastic case with paperwork and spent shell, all the back straps, three 8 rounds mags along with four 14 round mags.
